## Description

The current `ErrorBoundary.jsx` is minimal:

```jsx
class ErrorBoundary extends React.Component {
  state = { hasError: false };
  static getDerivedStateFromError() { return { hasError: true }; }
  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) return <div>Something went wrong.</div>;
    return this.props.children;
  }
}
```
It doesn't use the existing ErrorBoundary.css (which has beautiful styling), provides no recovery actions, and doesn't log errors. Additionally, AppRoutes.jsx has a duplicate /settings route.
Requirements
- Full error recovery UI using existing CSS
- "Try Again" (reset state) and "Reload Page" buttons
- Expandable technical error details
- Error logging to localStorage with context
- withErrorBoundary HOC for wrapping individual components
- Remove duplicate /settings route

## Description

The `HistoryPage.jsx` currently only shows a count of history items:

```jsx
const HistoryPage = () => {
  const { history } = useHistory();
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>History ({history.length} items)</h1>
    </div>
  );
};
```
Additionally, the useHistory.js hook has a bug: it reads from 'snappass_history' in localStorage, but sessionManager.js writes to 'passport_history'. History never loads.
Requirements
- Display all saved sessions with date, size, background, and status
- Search/filter sessions by size, background, or date
- Delete individual sessions
- Clear all sessions with confirmation dialog
- Empty state when no sessions exist
- Fix the localStorage key mismatch
